-- American Eagle names Levi's exec CEO
-- 
-- Tue Nov 15, 2011 5:48pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/11/15/us-americaneagle-idUSTRE7AE2QP20111115

 

 (Reuters) - Teen apparel retailer American Eagle Outfitters Inc ( AEO.N ) on Tuesday named Levi Strauss LEVST.UL executive Robert Hanson as chief executive, replacing Jim O'Donnell, who is retiring. 
 Hanson, 48, had been global president of the Levi's brand. O'Donnell announced his decision to retire in March. (Reporting by  Brad Dorfman  in Chicago; Editing by  Richard Chang )